The NPC will play animations to guide the ship to the "guide position".The Ship's Position is the Ship's Origin.The Guide Position is the Landing Pad's origin, plus the "TargetHeight" input value.OffsetThreshold - Horizontal area around "guide position" An OffsetThreshold value of "2" will give a 2 meter area around the Guide Position on the horizontal planeAngleThreshold - Angular threshold between the angle of the landing pad and the ship An AngleThreshold value of "15" allows the ship to be anywhere between 0 and 15 degrees offset to the angle of the landing pad.RangeThreshold - The furthest distance away from the landing pad that the NPC will consider using most other guide animations. A RangeThreshold of "50" means the NPC will only perform animations such as "move left" if the ship is within 50 meters of the Guid Position. If the ship is further away than this, they will only play the "moveTo" animation.TargetHeight - This sets the guide position above the origin of the landing pad.
Check to see if the animation fragment string from the ship alignment check has changed. If it has changed, play the "holdPosition" fragment. If not, continue playing the relevant fragment.
